26/07/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The EU and BiH signed an agreement Monday (25 July) under which the EU will provide 49.4m euros in aid to the Balkan nation under the CARDS programme for 2005. 
The money will be used to "facilitate integration of refugees, support reform of public administration, and it will provide further support to judicial and police reform", the head of the European Commission's mission to Bosnia, Michael Humphreys, told journalists. 
The EU has so far provided 2.6 billion euros in aid to BiH under various programmes. 
(Nezavisne novine - 26/07/05; AFP, PBS BiH - 25/07/05)
